<DOC><DOCNO>WSJ900810-0115</DOCNO><DOCID>900810-0115.</DOCID><HL>   Polaroid Will Build   Bedford, Mass., Plant   For New Product Line</HL><DATE>08/10/90</DATE><SO>WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), PAGE C9</SO><CO>   PRD</CO><LP>   CAMBRIDGE, Mass. -- Polaroid Corp. announced it will builda $90 million plant in New Bedford, Mass., to manufactureadvanced films for the company's new electronic imagingproducts.   The new, 250,000 square foot manufacturing facility,expected to be in operation by late 1992, will employ morethan 100 people in producing a &quot;wide range of new products,including advanced film for our new laser-based medicaldiagnostic imaging system known as Helios,&quot; said I.MacAllister Booth, Polaroid president and chief executiveofficer.</LP><TEXT>   The first product in its Helios line will be a specializedlaser printer for use with ultrasound and nuclear medicinescanners. The printer will make hard-copy images forexamination within 90 seconds, the company said. Currently,such images take up to 20 minutes to develop.   Polaroid said its Helios line is aimed initially atseizing a piece of the $3 billion world-wide annual marketfor medical-imaging film. The products will target theapproximately 25% of the market devoted to film used withelectronic and computerized imaging systems, such asultrasound and magnetic resonance imaging, or MRI, scanners.Future Helios products will be aimed at graphic artsapplications and scientific uses, such as seismic imaging.   Polaroid has suffered from steadily weakening sales sincethe decline of the instant photography market in the 1970s.</TEXT></DOC>